    "Consequently, we have included an additional category labeled \"Hybrid\" to the classification scheme, which is illustrated in Fig. 28.As depicted in Fig.",
    "28, the primary approaches for social network anonymization comprise \"Graph Modification,\" \"Generalization/Clustering,\" \"Differential Privacy,\" \"Uncertain Graphs,\" \"Cryptography,\" and \"Hybrid.\"",
    "We will delve into each of these approaches, along with their respective subcategories, in the subsequent paragraphs.",
    "Graph modificationThis approach involves altering the structure of the social network graph to obscure the identities, relationships, attributes, or all for individuals while preserving the overall network structure.",
    "This can be done through various techniques like edge modification (addition, deletion or altering links), node modification (addition, deletion or altering nodes), or a combination of both [19,21]."
